## Tech Stack
- Framework:  Next.js 15, App Router, TypeScript
- Styling:    Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS variable-based config in globals.css)
- Animation:  Framer Motion (spring physics, layout, AnimatePresence, motion values)
- Scroll:     Lenis (smooth scroll) + GSAP ScrollTrigger (parallax, reveals)
- Fonts:      Geist Mono (engineer) + Playfair Display italic (filmmaker) + Geist Sans

## Design System
### Dual accent identity
| Context     | Color   | Hex       | Used for                    |
|-------------|---------|-----------|----------------------------|
| Engineer    | Green   | #00ffaa   | Hover, glow, matrix rain    |
| Filmmaker   | Orange  | #ff6b35   | Hover, gradients, film tone |

### Palette
- Background:  #050505 (near-black)
- Foreground:  #f0f0f0 (off-white)
- Muted text:  #666666
- Glass bg:    rgba(255,255,255,0.04–0.08)
- Glass border: rgba(255,255,255,0.08–0.18)

### Typography rule
- Mono font  → anything "code": UI chrome, labels, taglines, project tags
- Serif font → anything "cinematic": hero main words, editorial headings
- NEVER mix them in the same text block without a deliberate contrast reason

### Motion principles
- Spring physics everywhere: stiffness 300–400, damping 24–30
- No linear or ease-in-out for primary interactions — always spring
- Hardware-accelerated: `will-change: transform` on animated elements
- Glassmorphism: backdrop-filter blur(20–24px) + saturate(180–200%)
- Text effects: ENGINEER → matrix/scanline green; FILMMAKER → warm gradient + film grain

